com.facebook.buck.cli

Class FakeBuckConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.cli.FakeBuckConfig

  • public class FakeBuckConfig
extends Object
    Implementation of BuckConfig with no data, or only the data specified by FakeBuckConfig(Map). This makes it possible to get an instance of a BuckConfig without reading .buckconfig files from disk. Designed exclusively for testing.

      • createFromFiles

        public static com.facebook.buck.cli.BuckConfig createFromFiles(ProjectFilesystem projectFilesystem,
                                               Iterable<File> files)
                                                        throws IOException
        Takes a sequence of .buckconfig files and loads them, in order, to create a BuckConfig object. Each successive file that is loaded has the ability to override definitions from a previous file.
        Parameters:
        projectFilesystem - project for which the BuckConfig is being created.
        files - The sequence of .buckconfig files to load.
        Throws:
        IOException
